tldr: The user requested to add a database, admin dashboard, and authentication
  to a sleep questionnaire application. I implemented these features, including
  a Prisma schema, API routes, and a Next.js middleware-based authentication
  system. During testing, a minor issue with form submission was identified.
overview: The user aimed to enhance a sleep questionnaire application by
  integrating a database for response storage, an admin dashboard for data
  access, and an authentication system. The approach involved updating the
  application's data models and forms to capture expanded demographic data,
  implementing a Prisma-backed PostgreSQL database (NeonDB), and developing API
  endpoints for data submission and retrieval, including CSV export. A simple
  password-based authentication system was built using Next.js middleware to
  secure the admin dashboard and data access routes. While the core features
  were implemented and the database schema was successfully applied, initial
  browser testing revealed an issue where the questionnaire form's submission to
  the database was not consistently triggered, which remained an open point at
  the end of the interaction.
